x4freetext: Neutron flux at an angle 30 degrees relative to
proton beam was used. Gas tritium target thickness -
60 keV, current on the target 0.4 microA, pulse
Time of flight method with the time resolution
2.25 nsec/m, flight path 2.84 m.  Ring geometry.
Scintillation liquid in Al cylinder of 10 cm
diameter, 5 cm height, equipped by photomultiplier
FEU-63, protected by lead and thick layer of paraffin
Detection relative efficiency was measured and
Double diff. inel. scat. cs. (spectra) are given in
arbitrary units.  Diff. elast. and inel. scat. cs.
The experimental neutron spectra were analyzed for
determining the nuclear temperature and the nuclear
The measured neutron spectra were corrected by the
dead time of the electronic scheme
The neutron spectra error (10-20 %) consists of
statistical error, the error of detector efficiency and
